column42:
The authenticated user may view a list of targeted file names before being uploaded to salesforce;
The authenticated user may view a list of targeted existing file names that have already been uploaded to a particular record;
Salesforce system administrator can configure the library to restrict the file types that can be uploaded by the authenticated end user;
Restrict authenticated end users from uploading multiple files, or alternatively allow authenticated users to upload multiple files;
Require authenticated users to upload at least one file before proceeding to the next screen in a screen flow, and prompt them with a custom message if they do not;
Allow authenticated users to cancel a planned upload of file(s) immediately in the UI;
Allow authenticated users to set the file name of files planned for upload;
Allows system administrators for full control over most aspects of the UX within the File Upload Improved library
